Nd2 Bf7 $1 {[%cal Gd6h6] Clearing the queen's path to the kingside.} 15. Nc3 {
White starts fighting for the d5-square, but his incomplete development does
not help him much.} (15. Nc4 {just takes the knight away from the kingside
defence and is comfortably met with} Qh6 {. Maybe White had overlooked that}
16. Ne5 {loses a pawn to} Bd6 $1) (15. Nc5 {allows many attacking options,
such as} Qg6 ({and} 15... Nf4 $5 16. Bf1 (16. exf4 Nxd4) 16... Qg6 17. exf4
Nxd4 18. Qc3 Nf3+ 19. Nxf3 Rxd1 20. Ne5 Qh5 $40) 16. Nxb7 Nxd4 $1 17. exd4 Nf4
18. Bf1 Nh3+ 19. Kh1 Nxf2+ 20. Kg1 Rxd4 $1 21. Kxf2 Qb6 $19) 15... Qh6 16. Nxd5
Bxd5 17. Bc4 Kh8 18. Bxd5 Rxd5 $15 {Now we have a French Defence type of
