to create some threats as soon as possible.} axb4 21. axb4 Rd7 {[%csl Bc7]
[%cal Be7d6]} (21... b5 $15 {[%cal Rb4b5,Gd6g6] was another good option.}) 22.
Bd2 {After this move White's play will soon run into a dead end.} (22. b5 Nb4)
(22. Ba3 $5 {[%cal Gb4b5,Ga3e7] Black could try} b5 $5 {[%csl Ga3] but then
the weaknesses along the c-file would reduce his attacking potential.} 23. Ng3
{[%cal Gg3e2]} f4 24. exf4 Nxd4 25. Qxe4 Qxf4 26. Qxf4 Rxf4) 22... Bd6 (22...
Nxb4 $2 23. Bxb4 Bxb4 24. Qa4 $18) (22... Bxb4 23. d5 Rxd5 24. Bxb4 Nxb4 25.
Qxc7 $44) 23. b5 Ne7 24. Ra7 b6 25. Rda1 Qe6 $1 {Black cannot, but also does
not need to attack anymore. The control over the d5-square and the possibility
