$14 {with space advantage for White, although Black is very solid and flexible.
}) 1... Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. e4 {[#] This is the
Boleslavsky approach. We also see this pawn structure (d3-e4 or d6-e5 with
