Gg1g8]}) 33. Kf3 Nf4 34. Rfc1 $1 (34. Nd5 Nxd5 35. exd5 Rg5 $132) 34... Rf8 (
34... Nxd3 35. Rc8+ Rxc8 36. Rxc8+ Kf7 37. Rb8 $16 {[%csl Rf6][%cal Rb8b7]})
35. Rc8 $6 (35. Nd5 $1 Nxd3 (35... Nxd5 36. exd5 $16 {/+-}) 36. Rd1 Nf4 37.
Nxf4 exf4 38. Rxd4 $16) 35... Rgf7 $1 36. Rg1+ (36. Nd5 Nxd3 37. Rg1+ Kh8 (
37... Rg7 $4 38. Nxf6+) 38. Rc2 Rd7 39. Rd2 Nf4 $14) 36... Kh8 (36... Rg7 $1
37. Rxf8+ (37. Rgc1 Rgf7) 37... Kxf8 38. Rc1 Rf7 $1 39. Nd5 Nxd3 40. Rb1 Rd7 $5
41. Rb3 Ne1+ 42. Ke2 Ng2 $132) 37. Rc2 Rd8 (37... Nxd3 38. Nd5 Rd7 39. Rd1 Nf4
40. Nxf4 exf4 41. Kxf4 $14 {[%cal Yd1d3,Ye4e5]}) 38. Nd5 Nxd5 (38... Nxd3 39.
Rd1 Nf4 40. Nxf4 exf4 41. Kxf4 $36 {, this is similar to 37...Nxd3.}) 39. exd5
Rfd7 40. Rgc1 Rxd5 41. Rc8 Kg7 $5 {Navara seeks active counterplay.} (41...
R5d7 42. Rxd8+ (42. R1c7 Rxc8 43. Rxd7 Rc2 $132) 42... Rxd8 43. Rc7 b5 44. Rc6
Kg7 45. h4 $1 $44 {[%cal Rf3e4,Rh4h6,Rc6c7] White still has excellent winning
chances.} (45. Rxa6 Rc8)) 42. Rxd8 Rxd8 43. Rc7+ Kh6 44. Rxb7 Rc8 (44... Rg8 $5
45. h4 (45. Rb6 Rg1 46. Rxf6+ Kg5 47. Rxa6 Kxf5 48. b5 Re1 49. b6 Rb1 $1 (49...
Re3+ $2 50. Kf2 Rxd3 51. Ra4 $18 {[%cal Rb6b7,Ra4b4]}) 50. a4 Rb3 $132) (45.
Rf7 Rg1 (45... Kg5 $2 46. Ke4) 46. Rxf6+ Kg5 {- 45.Rb6}) 45... Rg1 46. Rb6 Re1
$132 {is a line we will yet see below.}) 45. h4 (45. Rf7 Rc1 46. Kg4 $1 {
White didn't have this option after 44...Rg8!?, now he has winning chances:} (
46. Rxf6+ Kg5 47. Rxa6 Kxf5 48. b5 Re1 {-44...Rg8!?}) 46... Rg1+ 47. Kh4 $36)
45... Rc1 46. Ke4 (46. Rb6 $5 {It seems that Black can still hold after is a
dangerous try:} Re1 $1 (46... Kg7 47. Rxa6 Re1 48. Ra7+ Kh6 49. Rf7 Re3+ 50.
Kg4 Rxd3 51. Rxf6+ Kg7 52. Rd6 e4 (52... Rxa3 53. f6+ Kf7 54. Kf5 d3 55. b5 $18
) 53. f6+ Kh6 54. h5 Rxa3 (54... e3 55. Rd8 Rd1 56. f7 Rg1+ 57. Kf3 Rf1+ 58.
Ke2 Rf2+ 59. Ke1 Rxf7 60. b5 $18) 55. Rxd4 Rf3 56. Rxe4 Rxf6 57. b5 $18 {
[%cal Ye4e5,Yg4b4]}) 47. Rxf6+ (47. Rxa6 Kh5 $1 $13) 47... Kh5 48. Rxa6 Re3+
49. Kf2 Rxd3 50. Re6 (50. a4 e4 51. Re6 Rf3+ 52. Ke1 Re3+ 53. Kd1 Rd3+ 54. Kc2
Rc3+ 55. Kb2 e3) (50. Ke2 e4 (50... Rh3 $5) 51. Re6 Re3+ 52. Kd2 Rd3+ 53. Kc2
Rc3+ 54. Kb2 Re3 55. b5 Re2+ 56. Kb3 d3 57. b6 d2 58. Rd6 e3 59. b7 Re1 60. Kb2
e2 61. b8=Q Rb1+ 62. Kxb1 e1=Q+ 63. Ka2 d1=Q 64. Rxd1 Qxd1 {and the engine
claims a draw here!}) 50... Rxa3 51. Rxe5 Ra4 52. b5 (52. Rb5 Kxh4 53. f6 Kg4
