{[#]} 7. c5 $1 {In positions where White has pawns on c3, c4, and d4, this
advance is the most typical attempt of creating dynamic chances. Otherwise, in
the long run, Black will put an annoying pressure on c4.} dxc5 $2 ({Black
should have tried to keep the position closed by means of} 7... e4) {At this
point, White should have played} 8. dxe5 $1 ({The game went} 8. Ba3 $6 Nd7 9.
Qa4 $44 {when White has just enough compensation for the pawn.}) 8... Qxe5 9.
Qb3 $16 {with a huge pressure.} 1-0

