{[#] A subtle idea. As we know, in this structure, c5 is the perfect square
for the knight. The vulnerable b3-pawn will only increase the power of the
knight.} 14... Nb8 $1 {[%csl Rb3,Ge4][%cal Gb8d7,Gd7c5,Gc5e4,Gc5b3]} 15. Rd1
Nbd7 16. h3 Nc5 {Black is perfectly fine. He has a good control of the
position.} 17. Be3 Bc6 {[%cal Gf6d5,Gc4d5,Gc6d7] Stopping any b3-b4 ideas.
Additionally, after exchanging the d5-knight, Black will put his bishop on d7.}
18. Bd4 Nxd5 19. cxd5 Bd7 20. Rdb1 Qg5 1/2-1/2

