1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 Bc5 4. Bg2 a6 5. e3 d6 6. Nge2 Ba7 7. d3 {Giri keeps
the king in the center, but nevertheless} h5 $5 8. h3 (8. h4 {this is the
safest move for White. With a king still on e1, the advance "g7-g5" is not
that strong, but Black has a very comfortable position after the simple} Nf6
$11) 8... f5 (8... h4 {is more accurate} 9. g4 f5) 9. h4 ({A good plan here is
to start preparing the evacuation of the king on the queenside after:} 9. Bd2
$5 Nf6 10. Qb3 {[%cal Re1c1] followed by}) 9... Nf6 10. d4 O-O 11. b3 (11. dxe5
dxe5 12. Qxd8 Rxd8 $15 {This seems acceptable initially, but when you take a
closer look at the position, you see that White has too many weak squares. I
believe that Black is better in all those endgames.}) 11... f4 $1 {logical and
strong decision by Michael} 12. dxe5 (12. gxf4 exd4 13. Nxd4 (13. Bxc6 bxc6 14.
Nxd4 Qe8) 13... Nxd4 14. exd4 Bg4 $15) 12... f3 $1 {The point of Black's
previous move} 13. Bxf3 Nxe5 14. Bg2 (14. Nf4 $1 Nxf3+ 15. Qxf3 c6 16. O-O (16.
Nxh5 $4 Qa5 {is winning a piece}) 16... Bf5 $44 {The knight on "f4" is holding
the kingside for the moment, but still Black has a decent compensation and
chances to organize an attack on the kingside.}) 14... Bg4 $1 15. Bxb7 $4 {
A strange mistake by Anish. It is hard to say which move he missed, but
White's position is falling apart.} (15. O-O {was the only move that keeps
White in the game.} Nf3+ 16. Kh1 c6 $1 17. Nf4 Nh2 (17... Nxh4 $5 18. f3 Nxg2
19. Kxg2 Bd7 {[%cal Rd8e8,Rg7g5] Black's position looks promising to me}) 18.
f3 Nxf1 19. Qxf1 Bd7 {White has enough compensation for the exchange, but
nothing more than that.}) 15... Nf3+ 16. Kf1 Qd7 $1 {[%cal Rg4h3]} 17. Kg2 Rab8
(17... Rae8 $19 {wins on a spot}) 18. Bd5+ Kh8 $5 19. Bb2 Rbe8 20. Nf4 $5 Nxh4+
$4 {Michael was too greedy. He wins a queen, but suddenly White's initiative
is very powerfull} (20... Ne5 $1 {This move ended the game. The following
variation is just an illustration of the danger of White's position.} 21. Qb1 (
21. f3 Nxd5 $19) 21... c6 22. Be4 Nxe4 23. Nxe4 Bf3+ 24. Kg1 Rxf4 $1 $19 25.
exf4 Nxc4 26. Ng5 Bxf2+ 27. Kxf2 Re2+ 28. Kg1 Qa7+ 29. Bd4 Qxd4+ 30. Kf1 Qf2#)
21. Rxh4 Bxd1 22. Rxd1 $1 g5 $2 {this move losing on a spot} (22... Nxd5 $1 23.
Rxd5 $1 Kg8 24. Rdxh5 Re5 $8 25. Rh8+ Kf7 26. R8h7 $16 {White has multiple
threats, but Black's position is still holdable.} (26. Rxf8+ Kxf8 27. Ng6+ Kf7
28. Nxe5+ dxe5 $11)) 23. Ne4 $3 $18 gxh4 24. Bxf6+ Kh7 25. Rh1 $1 {the point
of White's idea} Rxe4 $2 (25... Qf5 {was Black's best chance, but still White
can win after:} 26. Rxh4 Rxf6 27. Rxh5+ Kg7 28. Rxf5 Rxf5 29. Ne6+ Rxe6 30.
Bxe6 $18) 26. Bxe4+ Kg8 27. Bd5+ {now is over} Kh7 28. Nxh5 Kg6 29. Be4+ Kf7
30. Rxh4 c6 31. Rf4 Kg8 32. Bf5 {Amazing and very complicated game.} 1-0

