{[%evp 0,41,18,-8,2,-24,-24,-28,-29,-27,-29,-14,-14,-6,-11,-14,-20,-14,-14,-12,
-21,9,-4,-9,27,11,99,74,74,75,88,80,83,91,130,93,102,89,160,184,184,204,282,
278]} 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. g3 Nc6 4. Bg2 Bc5 5. e3 d6 6. Nge2 Bf5 7. d4 Bb6
8. h3 {It seems that Karen studyied Kortschnoj's games} O-O 9. d5 Nb8 10. g4
Bg6 11. Ng3 Nfd7 {Here the Armenian GM decided that 0-0, Kh2, f2-f4 would be
too slow and decides to exploit the akward position of the "g6" bishop} 12. h4
$1 h5 ({If} 12... h6 {we can follow Kortschnoj's idea} 13. g5 hxg5 14. hxg5
Qxg5 15. e4 Qf6 16. Nf5 {[%cal Rd1g4,Rg4h3] Not the only move, but the one
which wins faster.} Bxf5 17. Qh5 {And the tricks are not helping Black to
survive} Bxf2+ (17... Bh3 18. Bf3 $3 {[%cal Rh1h3]}) 18. Ke2 $3 $18) (12... f5
{is not helping as well} 13. h5 $18) 13. gxh5 Bh7 14. h6 gxh6 15. e4 $18 Kh8
16. Bh3 Rg8 17. Bf5 Qf6 18. Qh5 Bxf5 19. exf5 Qg7 20. Bxh6 Bxf2+ 21. Ke2 $1 {
Nice finish and amazing performance by GM Grigoryan. This game is an example
why you should study the "classics"} 1-0

