1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. g3 Bc5 5. Bg2 d6 6. O-O O-O 7. d3 h6 8. a3 a6
9. b4 Ba7 10. Bb2 Be6 11. Nd2 Qd7 ({There is nothing wrong with the immediate} 
11... d5 12. cxd5 Nxd5 13. Rc1 Nxc3 14. Bxc3 Bd5 $11 {Black even took the
initiative later, but the game ended in a draw in ½-½ (60) Lautier,J (2550)
-Sokolov,I (2570) Wijk aan Zee 1991}) 12. Nd5 Ne8 $5 (12... Nh7 $1 {The
engines prefer this square, leaving "e8" for the rook}) 13. Rc1 Nd8 {Typical
idea, Black is ready to kick the knight from d5. Also, the knight from d8 is
going to "e6"} 14. Nc3 Bh3 {It is always useful to exchange the kingside's
defender before playing f7-f5} 15. e3 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Ne6 17. Ne2 c6 18. Nf3 Rd8
(18... f5 $6 {is premature due to} 19. c5 $1 $14) 19. e4 (19. c5 $6 f6 $1 $15)
(19. Qc2 $1 {was better, with approximately equal position}) 19... f5 $1 {
Black immediately initiative pawn contact and open the "f" file} 20. Nh4 f4 (
20... fxe4 21. dxe4 Ng5 $17 {[%cal Rd7h3]}) 21. f3 Be3 (21... fxg3 $1 22. hxg3
Be3 {[%cal Re3g5]}) 22. Rc2 Ng5 23. Nf5 Rxf5 $5 {This sacrifice looks good,
but even stronger was} (23... d5 $1) 24. exf5 Qxf5 25. g4 Qe6 26. Nc3 d5 27.
cxd5 cxd5 28. Bc1 d4 29. Bxe3 dxe3 30. Qe2 Nf6 31. Ne4 Ngxe4 $4 {This moves
lost all the advantage} (31... Nfxe4 $1 {This ended the game immediately} 32.
dxe4 Qd7 $19 {[%cal Rg5e6]}) 32. dxe4 h5 33. h3 Rd4 34. Rd1 hxg4 35. hxg4 Nd7
36. b5 Qd6 $4 (36... axb5 $1 $11) 37. Rc8+ (37. Rxd4 $1 {wins immediately} exd4
(37... Qxd4 38. bxa6 $18) 38. Qc4+ $18) 37... Kf7 38. Qa2+ Kg6 $4 (38... Kf6 $1
$11 {Black still can hold}) 39. Rxd4 exd4 40. Re8 Kf6 41. g5+ $4 {This was a
rapid game, and both players were in time trouble, so all those blunders are
easy to be explained} (41. Qg8 $1 $18) 41... Kxg5 42. Qf7 g6 (42... Qg6 $1 43.
Qxd7 Kh6+ 44. Kf1 e2+ 45. Kxe2 Qg2+ 46. Kd1 Qf1+ $11 {with a perpetual}) 43.
Re6 Ne5 44. Qf6+ {with mate to follow} 1-0

