[PlyCount "23"]

{[#]} 24. c5 $5 {This time, the sacrifice only offers practical chances.} (24.
Nfd2 $14 {would have retained some advantage, although the technical process
would have been anything but easy.}) 24... fxg3 $2 {An important positional
concession. Black must have felt relieved to get rid of one of his pawns
placed on dark squares while weakening the enemy kingside a bit. However,
capturing away from the centre helps White from a structural point of view.} (
24... dxc5 $1 25. Nxe5 Qc8 26. Qa6 Qf5 27. Nc4 Bxa1 28. Qxa1 Nd5 29. Qa8 Nhf6
30. Qf8 Qe6 31. Nxf6+ Nxf6 $13) (24... bxc5 $2 25. b6 $18) 25. hxg3 Qg4 $2 {
The start of a desperate attack.} (25... dxc5 $5 26. Nxe5 Qc8 27. Qa6 Qf5 28.
Nc4 Bxa1 29. Qxa1 Nd5 30. Qa8 Nhf6 31. Qf8 Qe6 32. Nxf6+ Nxf6 {In the absence
of the pawn on f4, White can consolidate his centre.} 33. e4 $16 Nxe4 34. Qd8
Qf7 35. dxe4 Qxc4 36. Qxc7+ Kg8 37. Qxb6 Qxe4+ 38. Kh2 Qf5 (38... Qf3 39. Qb8+
Kf7 40. Qc7+ Kg8 41. Qxc5) 39. Qb8+ Kg7 40. Qb7+ Kg8 41. Kg2 $18 {White's
passed pawn runs much faster than Black's.}) 26. cxd6 Nf4+ 27. Kg1 cxd6 28.
Nxd6 Neg6 29. Ne8 Nxe2+ 30. Kf1 Nxg3+ 31. fxg3 Ne7 32. Nxg7 Qa4 33. Qxe7 Qxa1+
34. Kg2 g4 35. Nf5+ {Thiede,L (2504)-Czarnota,P (2554) Germany 2007 (1-0, 35)}
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
