[Annotator "GM Mihail Marin"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "R7/1Qpqnrbk/1p1pbn2/1P2pp1p/2P3p1/2NP2P1/1B1NPPBP/6K1 w - - 0 22"]
[PlyCount "12"]

{[#]White's attack seems to be very advanced, but at the same time, he does
not have concrete threats yet. Black still needs regrouping, but when he will
launch his attack it will be very consistent.} 22. e3 $6 {For unknown reasons,
White starts defending instead of looking for active ideas.} (22. Ra7 $1 {
Forces Black to move with a knight in order to defend c7, thus making the
d5-square more accessible.} Bh6 23. e3 Ng6 24. Qc6 Qd8 25. Nd5 $1 Nxd5 26. Bxd5
Bxd5 27. Qxd5 Qe8 28. Kf1 $5 {It is a good idea to wait for the best moment
for the queenside break. We will see the merits of this quiet move soon.} (28.
c5 dxc5 29. Nc4 Re7 30. Ra8 Qf7 31. Qxf7+ Rxf7 32. Nxe5 Nxe5 33. Bxe5 Bg7 34.
Bf4 Rd7 $11) 28... h4 (28... Re7 {takes measures against c4-c5, but gives up
the attacking ideas.} 29. Nb1 $16 {[%cal Gb1c3,Gd5c6,Gc3d5] followed by Nc3,
Qc6 and Nd5.}) 29. c5 $1 dxc5 (29... hxg3 $5 30. Ra8 g2+ 31. Kxg2 Qe7 32. cxd6
cxd6 33. Nc4 f4 34. Nxd6 $16) 30. Nc4 Re7 (30... hxg3 31. Nd6 $1 $18) 31. Ra8
Qf7 32. Qxf7+ Rxf7 33. gxh4 $1 $16 {Suddenly, Black is defenceless against
h4-h5, dooming the pawn on e5.}) 22... h4 {Black's attack is very consistent
now.} 23. Ne2 h3 $1 {Suddenly, White will have back rank problems.} 24. Bf1 (
24. Bh1 d5 25. Bxe5 dxc4 26. Nf4 Bd5 27. Nxd5 Nfxd5 $17) 24... Ng6 25. d4 (25.
Qc6 d5 $15) 25... f4 26. exf4 exf4 27. gxf4 d5 {Van Wely,L (2625)-Movsesian,S 
(2751) Wijk aan Zee 2009 (0-1, 44)} *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
