Be6 $1 $146 {Development!} 12. Ba3 (12. c5 $2 dxc5 13. Nxe5 Ne8 $1 $19 {Psakhis
}) ({During the webinar, one of the questions was what if} 12. Nd2 {in order
to induce} Rb8 {and gain a tempo.} ({My live reaction was} 12... d5 $2 {
, which appears to be recommended by Psakhis. In fact tjis is just bad.} 13.
cxd5 Nfxd5 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Bb2 $16) 13. Ba3 {White's extra tempo is not
helping at all. Since there is no more pressure on e5, c4-c5 ceases to be a
threat and Black can continue his plan without playing ...b7-b6.} g5 $5) 12...
Rc8 $1 {A paradoxical move, aimed at inhibiting c4-c5.} (12... b6 $2 13. Nxe5
