problems after this move.} (13. c5 $5 b6 14. cxd6 cxd6 15. Qd2 Qd7 16. Rfc1 g5
17. Na2 $1 $132 {/\ Nb4 ><c6}) ({I have analysed two somewhat mysterious moves,
preparing the not less mystearious e2-e4. The point is that White needs to
open the centre somehow, since on the queenside there is not much going on.} 
13. Re1 $5 $146 g5 14. e4 f4 (14... fxe4 15. dxe4 Bxc4 16. Nxe5 $1 {Based on
